The paper proposes a method to dynamically apply convolutions conditioned on the input image, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves training a gating branch using the Gumbel-Softmax trick, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the method, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper provides an efficient CUDA implementation of the method, which is a topic in computer systems and architecture (cs.CL).
